  --> Java Config Bean
       -> Make an existing third-party class available to spring framework.
       -> Create a Java class and annotate as a @Configuration. This is basically a
          configuration class for configuring spring using custom approach.
       -> Define @Bean method to configure the bean.(the bean id defaults to the method name.)
       -> Inject the bean to our controller.

  --> Hibernate JPA Overview.
       -> Hibernate handles all the low level SQL.
       -> Minimize the amount of JDBC code you have to develop.
       -> Hibernate provides the object to relational Mapping(ORM).
       -> entityManager.persist(*Object*) it is a special JPA helper object.